<h2 id="avoid-json-hijacking">Avoid JSON Hijacking <a class="headerlink" href="get-collection#avoid-json-hijacking" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Why? You can structure your JSON however you want, but by putting the collection
inside a key, we have room for more root keys later like maybe <code>count</code> or
<code>offset</code> for pagination. Second, your outer JSON should always be an object,
not an array. So, curly braces instead of square brackets. If you have square
brackets, you're vulnerable to something called JSON Hijacking. While not as bad
as a car hijacking is something you want to avoid.</p>
<h2 id="turning-the-programmers-into-json">Turning the Programmers into JSON <a class="headerlink" href="get-collection#turning-the-programmers-into-json" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
