<h2 id="returning-json-on-create">Returning JSON on Create <a class="headerlink" href="get-collection#returning-json-on-create" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Remember how we're returning a super-reassuring text message from our POST
endpoint? Well, you <em>can</em> do this, but usually, you'll return the resource
you just created. That's easy now - so let's do it. Just, <code>$data = $this-&gt;serializeProgrammer()</code>.
Then <code>json_encode()</code> that in the Response. And don't forget to set the
<code>Content-Type</code> header:</p>
