</p>
<p>API consistency is king, and this is just one less spot for me to mess up
and forget to set that header. Make sure you update the other spots,
which is pretty much a copy-and-paste operation - be careful to keep
the right status code.</p>
<p>Take out the extra <code>die()</code> statement in <code>testing.php</code> and let's try this
<em>whole</em> thing out:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">php testing.php</div></code></pre>
<p>It's lovely. To make sure it doesn't break, we need to add tests! And that
will be a whole lot more interesting than you think.</p>

    
